  "hangulS0L0Title": "How was Hangul born?",
  "hangulS0L0Subtitle": "A brief look at how Hangul was created",
  "hangulS0L0Step0Title": "Long ago, writing was very difficult",
  "hangulS0L0Step0Desc": "In the past, writing relied on Chinese characters (Hanja),\nmaking it difficult for most people to read and write.",
  "hangulS0L0Step0Highlights": "Hanja,Difficulty,Reading,Writing",
  "hangulS0L0Step1Title": "King Sejong created a new writing system",
  "hangulS0L0Step1Desc": "To help common people learn easily,\nKing Sejong personally created Hunminjeongeum.\n(Created in 1443, proclaimed in 1446)",
  "hangulS0L0Step1Highlights": "King Sejong,Hunminjeongeum,1443,1446",
  "hangulS0L0Step2Title": "And that became today's Hangul",
  "hangulS0L0Step2Desc": "Hangul is a writing system designed to easily represent sounds.\nIn the next lesson, we'll learn about consonant and vowel structure.",
  "hangulS0L0Step2Highlights": "Sound,Easy writing,Hangul",
  "hangulS0L0SummaryTitle": "Introduction complete!",
  "hangulS0L0SummaryMsg": "Great!\nNow you know why Hangul was created.\nLet's learn about consonant/vowel structure next.",
  "hangulS0L1Title": "Assembling the 가 block",
  "hangulS0L1Subtitle": "See how Hangul characters are built",
  "hangulS0L1IntroTitle": "Hangul works like blocks!",
  "hangulS0L1IntroDesc": "Hangul combines consonants and vowels to form characters.\nConsonant (ㄱ) + Vowel (ㅏ) = 가\n\nSome characters also have an extra consonant at the bottom, called batchim.\n(We'll learn that later!)",
  "hangulS0L1IntroHighlights": "Consonant,Vowel,Character",
  "hangulS0L1DragGaTitle": "Assemble 가",
  "hangulS0L1DragGaDesc": "Drag ㄱ and ㅏ into the empty slots",
  "hangulS0L1DragNaTitle": "Assemble 나",
  "hangulS0L1DragNaDesc": "Try using the new consonant ㄴ",
  "hangulS0L1DragDaTitle": "Assemble 다",
  "hangulS0L1DragDaDesc": "Try using the new consonant ㄷ",
  "hangulS0L1SummaryTitle": "Lesson Complete!",
  "hangulS0L1SummaryMsg": "Consonant + Vowel = Syllable block!\nㄱ+ㅏ=가, ㄴ+ㅏ=나, ㄷ+ㅏ=다",
  "hangulS0L2Title": "Sound Exploration",
  "hangulS0L2Subtitle": "Explore consonant and vowel sounds",
  "hangulS0L2IntroTitle": "Listen to the sounds",
  "hangulS0L2IntroDesc": "Each Hangul consonant and vowel has its own unique sound.\nListen carefully to each one.",
  "hangulS0L2Sound1Title": "Consonant sounds: ㄱ, ㄴ, ㄷ",
  "hangulS0L2Sound1Desc": "Each consonant is paired with vowel ㅏ to make a syllable: 가, 나, 다",
  "hangulS0L2Sound2Title": "ㅏ, ㅗ vowel sounds",
